16 "16-13-123.
17 (a) A processor shall register annually with the department any kratom product intended
18 to be offered for sale to an end consumer that is in an approved kratom delivery form and
19 pay a fee, adjusted annually, to cover all administrative costs for processing and
20 administering such registrations, including the necessary staff and the publication and
21 maintenance of a kratom registration web page as provided in this Code section.
22 (b) The registration shall include the following:
23 (1) Submission of a certificate of analysis from a certified independent third-party
24 laboratory showing compliance with the requirements of this article for kratom products;
25 and
26 (2) Sworn certification that:
27 (A) The kratom product was manufactured, processed, or held in a facility that holds
28 a current and valid food facility registration with the United States Food and Drug
29 Administration;
30 (B) The processor has a reasonable basis to believe that the kratom product is safe for
31 consumption under the conditions of use set forth on the label. The processor assumes
32 responsibility and liability for any such products offered for sale;
33 (C) The kratom product is not adulterated with any dangerous substance not derived
34 from kratom. A kratom product is adulterated with a dangerous substance not derived
35 from kratom if the kratom product contains a poisonous or otherwise deleterious
36 ingredient not derived from kratom, including, but not limited to, substances listed as
37 controlled substances under state or federal law;
38 (D) The kratom product does not contain any synthesized kratom alkaloid or kratom
39 constituent produced by using a manufacturing process that synthetically changes the
40 composition of any kratom alkaloid or kratom constituent as it is naturally found in the
41 kratom leaf, or any kratom alkaloids or other kratom constituents that have been
42 isolated or manipulated to increase their potency; and
