43 (E) The kratom product is not manufactured in a manner that is attractive to children.
44 (c) A kratom product that contains the same kratom ingredients in the same kratom
45 delivery form, but a different container, package, or volume, shall be included in a single
46 registration pursuant to subsection (a) of this Code section.
47 (d) By January 1, 2026, the department shall publish and maintain a kratom registration
48 page on its official public website listing all currently registered kratom products for sale
49 by retailers. Such website shall allow retailers to verify registered kratom products that
50 they are permitted to sell to consumers."
51 SECTION 3.
52 Said article is further amended in Code Section 16-13-122, relating to content of kratom and
53 required labeling, by revising subsections (f) and (g) as follows:
54 "(f)(1) A processor who knowingly or with criminal negligence commits an act in
55 violation of this Code section shall, upon a first conviction thereof, be guilty of a
56 misdemeanor of a high and aggravated nature, and upon a subsequent conviction, be
57 guilty of a felony, and shall be punished by imprisonment for not less than one year nor
58 more than 15 years, by a fine not to exceed $100,000.00, or both.
59 (2) A processor who negligently commits an act in violation of this Code section shall
60 be guilty of a misdemeanor and subject to a fine not to exceed $1,000.00.
61 (g)(1) A retailer who knowingly or with criminal negligence commits an act in violation
62 of subsection (a), (b), (c), or (e) of this Code section shall, upon a first conviction thereof,
63 be guilty of a misdemeanor of a high and aggravated nature, and upon a subsequent
64 conviction, be guilty of a felony, and shall be punished by imprisonment for not less than
65 one year nor more than 15 years six months nor more than two years, by a fine not to
66 exceed $100,000.00, or both.
67 (2) A retailer who negligently commits an act in violation of subsection (a), (b), (c),
68 or (e) of this Code section shall be guilty of a misdemeanor; provided, however, that, for
